import os

last_dir = os.listdir('models')[-1]
num = int(last_dir[3:]) + 1
os.mkdir('models/Run%d' % num)
...
ModelCheckpoint(filepath='models/Run%d/model_{epoch}' % num)

===================================================================================
If your 'models' directory is the following (for example):
Run1
Run2
Run325
This code creates directory named Run326, not Run4 as you may think.
Note: it is neccersary for your directory to be sorted.
